# Faker Server

### Prerequisites

You will need a node in your system.

- npm

  ```sh
  npm install npm@latest -g
  ```

- Verify Installation
  ```sh
  node -v
  ```

### Installation

1. Clone the Front-End repo

   ```sh
   git clone git@github.com:thearpitanand/faker-server.git
   ```

2. Install NPM packages

   ```sh
   npm i
   ```

3. Run the app in the development mode.

   ```sh
   npm start
   ```

4. Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) to run API.

### Routes

1. API Method: GET - Fetch Data

   ```sh
   http://localhost:3000/data
   ```

   ```sh
   Response: [
        {
            "userId":"cabfcea5-be9d-4835-be5c-6370f2879f06",
            "username":"Kaden_Kertzmann",
            "salary":"68641840"
        },
        {
            "userId":"cabfcea5-be9d-4835-be5c-6370f2879f06",
            "username":"Kaden_Kertzmann",
            "salary":"68641840"
        },
        {
            "userId":"cabfcea5-be9d-48HTTP request35-be5c-6370f2879f06",
            "username":"Kaden_Kertzmann",
